text: Mitrella aemulata is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae, the dove snails. ==Description== The length of the shell attains 7.7 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off the island of Annobón, Equatorial Guinea, West Africa.Rolán E. 2005. Columbellidae (Gastropoda, Neogastropoda) of the gulf of Guinea with the description of eight new species. Iberus 23(2): 119–156 ==References== * aemulata Category:Endemic fauna of Annobón Category:Invertebrates of Equatorial Guinea Category:Gastropods described in 2005
title: Mitrella aemulata
